    <title>Frequently Asked Questions - Fitness Challenge Tracker</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Get answers to frequently asked questions about Fitness Challenge Tracker. Learn about pricing, features, compatibility, and more.">
    
    <!-- JSON-LD Schema for FAQPage -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q1: How much does Fitness Challenge Tracker cost and what features are included?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Fitness Challenge Tracker offers three plans: Free (track 1 challenge, basic progress photos, community challenges), Pro ($7.99/month or $47.88/year, unlimited challenges, custom challenge creator, advanced analytics, nutrition tracking, Apple Health/Google Fit sync), and Coach ($19.99/month, client management, white-label reports, challenge templates library, group leaderboard). A 14-day free trial of Pro is included with signup. | Feature | Free | Pro | Coach | |---------|------|-----|-------| | Active challenges | 1 | Unlimited | Unlimited | | Custom challenges | — | ✓ | ✓ | | Analytics | Basic | Advanced | Advanced | | Nutrition tracking | — | ✓ | ✓ | | Client management | — | — | ✓ | | White-label reports | — | — | ✓ | | Price | $0 | $7.99/mo | $19.99/mo | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q2: What types of fitness challenges can I create or join?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Fitness Challenge Tracker supports 50+ challenge types: step challenges, plank challenges, push-up challenges, running challenges, hydration challenges, sleep challenges, nutrition challenges, meditation challenges, custom habit challenges, and team challenges. Users can create fully custom challenges with their own rules, duration, and tracking metrics. The library includes challenges for all fitness levels. - **Movement:** Steps, running, cycling, swimming, yoga, dance - **Strength:** Push-ups, planks, squats, pull-ups, custom workouts - **Wellness:** Sleep, hydration, meditation, screen time reduction - **Nutrition:** Water intake, protein target, veggie portions, meal prep - **Custom:** Define your own metric, rules, and duration ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q3: How do I track my progress and what metrics are available?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Track progress via manual entry, photo logging, Apple Health/Google Fit auto-sync, or wearable device integration (Apple Watch, Fitbit, Garmin). Metrics include: completion rate, streak length, improvement over time, before/after photos, weight/body composition, and custom metrics. The analytics dashboard visualizes trends with interactive charts and exportable reports. - **Manual entry:** Log reps, minutes, distance, or custom metric - **Photo logging:** Progress photos with pose guidance and privacy controls - **Auto-sync:** Apple Health, Google Fit, Fitbit, Garmin, Apple Watch - **Wearable:** Real-time tracking during workouts (heart rate, calories, zones) - Completion rate (% of challenge days completed) - Streak (current and longest) - Performance improvement (e.g., plank time: 30s → 2min) - Body metrics (weight, body fat %, measurements) - Habit consistency score (0–100) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q4: Which devices and platforms does Fitness Challenge Tracker work on?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Fitness Challenge Tracker works on iOS, Android, and web. It integrates with Apple Health, Google Fit, Fitbit, Garmin, and Apple Watch. The web version syncs with the mobile app in real time. An Apple Watch app is available; Wear OS app is in beta. All data syncs across devices automatically. | Platform | Status | Sync | |----------|--------|------| | iOS | ✓ | Real-time | | Android | ✓ | Real-time | | Web | ✓ | Real-time | | Apple Watch | ✓ | Real-time | | Fitbit | ✓ | Daily | | Garmin | ✓ | Daily | | Wear OS | Beta | Real-time | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q5: Is my fitness and health data private and secure?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Fitness Challenge Tracker is SOC 2 Type II certified, GDPR compliant, and HIPAA-compliant workflows are supported via BAA. Your health data is encrypted at rest (AES-256) and in transit (TLS 1.3). We never sell your data. You own your data and can export or delete it anytime. Progress photos are stored with zero-knowledge encryption (only you can view them). - SOC 2 Type II certified - GDPR compliant (EU users) - HIPAA compliant (BAA available on Coach plan) - Zero-knowledge photo storage (client-side encryption) - No data resale (contractually guaranteed) - Optional: local-only mode (Coach plan, data never leaves device) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q6: Can I create custom challenges with my own rules and metrics?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The custom challenge creator lets you define any tracking metric (reps, minutes, distance, boolean completion, or custom units), set challenge duration (1 day to 1 year), choose scoring mode (cumulative, daily target, or streak), add educational content, and set privacy (public, unlisted, or private). Pro users can save custom challenges as templates for reuse. - **Metric type:** Numeric (reps, minutes), boolean (done/not done), custom units (e.g., \"pages read\") - **Duration:** 1 day to 1 year - **Scoring mode:** Cumulative (total over period), daily target (hit X every day), streak (consecutive days) - **Content:** Add descriptions, tips, and resource links for each day - **Privacy:** Public (discoverable), unlisted (link only), private (you only) - **Template:** Save as reusable template (Pro feature) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q7: Does Fitness Challenge Tracker integrate with other fitness apps and devices?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Fitness Challenge Tracker integrates with 20+ fitness platforms: Apple Health, Google Fit, Fitbit, Garmin, Strava, MyFitnessPal, Nike Run Club, and more. The integrations work via OAuth (you authorize access, no password sharing). Data from connected apps automatically updates your challenge progress in real time. New integrations are added monthly based on user votes. - **Health Platforms:** Apple Health, Google Fit - **Wearables:** Fitbit, Garmin, Apple Watch, Whoop, Oura - **Apps:** Strava, MyFitnessPal, Nike Run Club, Adidas Running - **Gym Equipment:** Peloton, Tonal, Treadmill (via Fitbit) - **Automation:** Zapier (connect to 5,000+ apps) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q8: How does the community and social features work—can I join challenges with friends?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Fitness Challenge Tracker has a community of 500,000+ users. You can join public challenges, invite friends to private challenges, create team challenges (compete in groups), and share progress updates. The leaderboard shows top performers (with privacy controls). Community challenges include moderated discussions, daily tips, and motivation from fitness coaches. Social sharing to Instagram/Stories is supported with auto-generated graphics. - **Public challenges:** Browse and join challenges created by the community - **Private challenges:** Invite specific friends via link or email - **Team challenges:** Compete in teams (total score or average per person) - **Leaderboard:** See how you rank (opt out anytime) - **Community:** Discussion boards, motivation, coach tips - **Social sharing:** Auto-generated progress graphics for Instagram/Stories ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q9: What customer support and resources are available?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Free users get email support (72-hour response) and knowledge base access. Pro users receive priority email (24-hour response) and live chat. Coach users get phone support, 1-on-1 onboarding, and a dedicated account manager. All users can access 40+ video tutorials, the challenge idea library (500+ ideas), and weekly live Q&A sessions with fitness coaches. | Support Type | Free | Pro | Coach | |--------------|------|-----|-------| | Email support | ✓ (72hr) | ✓ (24hr) | ✓ (4hr) | | Live chat | — | ✓ | ✓ | | Phone support | — | — | ✓ | | 1-on-1 onboarding | — | — | ✓ | | Account manager | — | — | ✓ | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q10: How do I cancel my subscription and what happens to my challenge data?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cancel anytime from Account Settings—no phone call required. Your access continues until period end. We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee on annual plans. After cancellation, your challenge history is preserved for 6 months (reactive with one click). You can export all data (CSV, PDF) before canceling. Progress photos require separate export (privacy protection). - **Monthly plans:** Cancel anytime; no further billing; access until month-end - **Annual plans:** Full refund within 30 days; after 30 days, access continues until year-end - **Data retention:** 6 months after cancellation (soft delete) - **Data export:** CSV (numeric data), PDF (reports), ZIP (progress photos) - **Permanent deletion:** 6 months after cancellation (hard delete) ---"
      }
    }
  ]
}
